[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying server connections**\n\nI need to wait until the runner executes the accept function. Even before that, the server socket will be listening. The connect function will only work after the server socket has been created. Hmm, after writing the event, I wonder if I need to close the socket? The try-with statement should close the output, but let me ensure I'm following that correctly to avoid any issues later on.\n\n**Identifying serialization issues**\n\nI’m considering potential issues with native-image and Java serialization needing metadata for the LoggingEventVO classes. I notice that existing tests cover this but want to ensure further coverage for the readObject method when active. It's good that I've thought of this. I’m also noting that the \"RemoteAppenderStreamClient.run line 96 readObject\" call happens in the server thread, and the dynamic access reporter might trace it as covered if readObject is invoked. That's a solid plan!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05bbd23cbd80a707016a0582b350e881968b2e4e457d0a9167\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBYLGTxITIbDbJOxzPqIV0SxYEYFPUnmE1NgiPiIFJ7gq6l3xLEwkDLCOCBTnStQ7eZtRFJTEx-XvKWDsb7aOpreGRLL95ogBVM4aYgDOQpZ45pFZEWel3dw3UnbbPACURYbfPH1CvNKCZEKMY5K24lDoHblLC0Uhb8dyyMp4i9z6Cw5QV8MRZgH9dZGbrwWg3faP7kPofV6QD01fOwDgY4hHl0T2LZQosIZLdlH6z-cDdseqpMeKt4hgwbvssSYIO7bquRLq7Jvmc9oBAmkH_rTwLII1SCKte49Cx4tHTBkpMGilvNuRox-yKE1Xibf8I-qHQkzIjeLwBKCPEO8Uv5Y50Ou5xy5AKZrTmAO4Zg--Xo7GEbLoxDvjO9tVlqhm05BpTDTPTEsqo502D-HpIN_WIeKprgnC1YswPiwcQ8iEcG7WQMghJCxD958fqg0uCHsb5IkFE5b5g6jNXscRQmtgA09ZFhp1uU68gg3sYe3u0hzcDyVn_Jhi2F0XPqrjo35LPFukkFjKBo3pHCbvgg3vh5pXPV79Q0npN3pPHCuRbPqV51AK2r8Xv-ykyRf04KEz9oY7Q0n724RE5-Ruvjba5cFrvWHhFrZk-Lmdg2Gc7b5f1sZz6YQ8aHeomk072zfcyCqutfJNhva_gyYFd3axGhZRlTf9jbDnqhmkR-oyQhVOpKV9134TL_nmd-e9rjiAw9odfuGWRAUE34V3Hev0rUpfKVkuZm73sYEfEO0IN9uGR2v1RFGJjbHgiaJMgARNI56E4_IsMC0S